WEBVTT

00:02.135 --> 00:05.171
In New York City's war on crime,

00:05.171 --> 00:08.080
the worst criminal offenders
are pursued by the detectives

00:08.080 --> 00:09.609
of the Major Case Squad.

00:09.609 --> 00:12.407
These are their stories.

00:14.084 --> 00:15.502
They want it to end, Laura.

00:15.502 --> 00:18.772
It's not about the money.

00:18.772 --> 00:20.675
Honey, we have to let go.

00:20.675 --> 00:24.675
Well, maybe you can, but I can't.

00:26.060 --> 00:28.869
It's the heart of this community.
It's part of this community.

00:28.869 --> 00:31.050
You people don't seem to understand that.

00:31.050 --> 00:32.543
"You people"?

00:32.543 --> 00:36.803
Well, I hope you're there tomorrow
to tell "us people" that to our faces.

00:40.903 --> 00:44.415
How dare they!

00:44.415 --> 00:47.779
Rob, look at this.

00:47.779 --> 00:51.542
Oh, for cryin' out loud.
How much is Satan paying you?

00:52.042 --> 00:55.614
The church exercised their
last option five years ago.

00:55.614 --> 00:58.272
Nobody thought it would come to this.

00:58.272 --> 01:01.475
Hello, Mike. Where's Laura?

01:01.475 --> 01:04.458
Uh, she's still in the car.

01:04.458 --> 01:08.458
I'll go get her.

01:10.009 --> 01:13.237
Oh, Laura.

01:13.237 --> 01:17.135
- Sometimes I just can't stop.
- I know, I know.

01:17.635 --> 01:19.211
Everything all right, Ms. Hendrix?

01:19.211 --> 01:22.986
Yes, Connie. Thanks.

01:22.986 --> 01:26.744
Come on.
I'll buy you a sugar-free cookie.

01:26.744 --> 01:28.512
Okay.

01:30.217 --> 01:32.305
Like most of you,
Ginny and I don't want to join

01:32.305 --> 01:35.185
some big congregation off the island.

01:35.185 --> 01:39.185
That's not why we moved here to raise our kids.

01:39.718 --> 01:43.683
The Owners'Association wants to preserve
the character of this community, too,

01:43.683 --> 01:45.342
but it takes money.

01:45.342 --> 01:47.014
The city won't pay for improvements.

01:47.014 --> 01:49.713
The only thing you want to improve is your checkbook.

01:49.713 --> 01:52.247
How big a kickback you gettin'?

01:52.247 --> 01:54.950
Henry, that is a low blow.

01:54.950 --> 01:57.460
Well, at least he's not hiding.

01:57.460 --> 02:01.906
I want to know the coward who sent this.

02:01.906 --> 02:03.812
Dr. Ricci.!

02:03.812 --> 02:06.054
Dr. Ricci, there's something wrong with Laura.

02:06.054 --> 02:10.054
She's in the bathroom.
I think she's done something to herself.

02:12.115 --> 02:14.058
Get her started on norepinephrine.

02:14.058 --> 02:17.001
- Four megs, five percent.
- Yes, Doctor.

02:17.001 --> 02:21.046
Mr. Koehler,
we're treating your wife for poisoning,

02:21.046 --> 02:24.307
but we don't yet know what she ingested.

02:24.307 --> 02:27.390
Now, you told the nurse
you think she attempted suicide.

02:27.390 --> 02:29.516
Yeah, she's had a hard time lately.

02:29.516 --> 02:30.975
We have a suspected poisoning.

02:30.975 --> 02:32.896
Male, 73. B.P.'s crashed.

02:32.896 --> 02:35.119
Ipecac and lavage.
Let's get some blood.

02:35.119 --> 02:37.631
I'm sorry. Do you have any idea
what your wife might have taken?

02:37.631 --> 02:39.555
No. / Doctor, there's an ambulance
en route with another poisoning.

02:39.555 --> 02:41.540
- The patient's unresponsive.
- Call St. Lucia's.

02:41.540 --> 02:43.574
- Tell them we might need to transfer...
- Somebody help me!

02:43.574 --> 02:45.215
My wife's in the car.
She can't breathe.

02:45.215 --> 02:49.685
She's having convulsions.
Please help her!

