03:39.223 --> 03:41.313
Since last night,
there have been two more cases.

03:41.313 --> 03:44.846
That brings it to three dead, two in
a coma and four in critical condition.

03:44.846 --> 03:48.520
- All from arsenic?
- Right. The first victim, Laura Koehler,

03:48.520 --> 03:50.056
she's one of the deceased.

03:50.056 --> 03:51.623
Her husband thought it was a suicide.

03:51.623 --> 03:52.876
Then the others rolled in.

03:52.876 --> 03:55.067
The common denominator's
a meeting yesterday afternoon.

03:55.067 --> 03:56.160
They served food and drink?

03:56.160 --> 03:59.715
Yes. The reverend's wife was in charge of that.

03:59.715 --> 04:03.671
One of the injured got this in the mail.

04:03.671 --> 04:06.122
You caught yourself a live one.

04:06.122 --> 04:08.778
"How much is Satan paying you?"

04:08.778 --> 04:12.104
So much for reasoned debate.

04:12.604 --> 04:14.323
I bought the cookies from the island bakery.

04:14.323 --> 04:16.901
I made the coffee and the iced tea myself in the kitchenette.

04:16.901 --> 04:18.149
Didn't anyone help you?

04:18.149 --> 04:20.480
Some young girls from the parish.

04:20.480 --> 04:24.157
Uh, the meeting,
what was the controversy?

04:24.157 --> 04:27.139
The church is losing its lease.

04:27.139 --> 04:31.326
The Channel Island trustees want
to sell the land to a condo developer.

04:31.326 --> 04:33.221
Well, the island isn't big enough.

04:33.221 --> 04:36.147
I mean, there'd be no place
for the church to move to.

04:36.147 --> 04:38.093
That's right.

04:38.093 --> 04:40.953
One of the victims got this letter.

04:40.953 --> 04:44.304
I assume that she was for selling the property.

04:44.304 --> 04:46.735
Yes. Her husband, Rob, is a trustee.

04:46.735 --> 04:48.930
I don't agree with them,
but they're good people.

04:48.930 --> 04:52.089
Uh, what about the other victims on this list?

04:52.089 --> 04:53.359
Where did they stand?

04:53.359 --> 04:56.590
George Tooley, he was for the sale.

04:56.590 --> 04:59.100
Old Henry Leavitt,

04:59.100 --> 05:01.062
he was against.

05:01.062 --> 05:03.230
Laura Koehler,
I think she was against.

05:03.230 --> 05:07.870
For, for. Against.

05:10.894 --> 05:14.894
So much for narrowing the field.

05:16.364 --> 05:20.098
The lab found arsenic in 12
coffee cups retrieved from the trash.

05:20.098 --> 05:22.043
All the tainted coffee had artificial sweetener,

05:22.043 --> 05:24.170
as did the stomach contents of the victims.

05:24.170 --> 05:28.076
Someone could have steam-opened
the packets of sweetener and then resealed them.

05:28.576 --> 05:32.100
What about leftover packets?
Any of them tampered with?

05:32.100 --> 05:35.082
No, but the poisoner might've
picked them up at the end of the meeting.

05:35.082 --> 05:37.229
The victims were on both sides of the issue.

05:37.229 --> 05:40.396
The only thing they had in common
was artificial sweetener.

05:40.396 --> 05:42.851
The killer was targeting people on diets?

05:42.851 --> 05:44.673
Maybe not all of them were targets.

05:44.673 --> 05:46.920
There's one victim whose life
depended on avoiding sugar.

05:46.920 --> 05:50.377
Laura Koehler.

05:50.377 --> 05:51.708
She was a diabetic.

05:51.708 --> 05:55.955
The one whose husband was
pushing the suicide scenario.

05:55.955 --> 05:58.106
Home of Michael & Laura Koehler
Channel Island, New York
Wednesday, May 21

05:58.106 --> 06:01.566
When you found your wife unconscious,
you didn't suspect her diabetes?

06:01.566 --> 06:05.683
No, because she was always so careful.

06:05.683 --> 06:08.913
And suicide was more likely?

06:08.913 --> 06:10.367
Had she tried before?

06:10.367 --> 06:16.811
No, but things had gotten very difficult for her lately.

06:19.997 --> 06:24.505
We lost our son Brian in a drowning accident.

06:26.186 --> 06:27.985
Oh.

06:28.828 --> 06:31.817
That's right. I remember seeing
his photo in the newspaper.

06:31.817 --> 06:33.736
It was four months ago.

06:33.736 --> 06:35.820
Your son and two other boys,

06:35.820 --> 06:39.820
they were taking a boat to Hart Island.

06:41.140 --> 06:43.685
There's... There's a lawsuit,
isn't there, against the State?

06:43.685 --> 06:47.075
You and the other parents
are suing over the 911 system?

06:47.075 --> 06:50.858
Brian tried to call 911 on his cell phone
when the boat started sinking.

06:51.358 --> 06:55.358
But those people, they never sent help.

06:56.092 --> 06:58.055
Are you suing anyone else?

06:58.055 --> 07:00.405
McCarter's Marina.

07:00.405 --> 07:03.287
That's where they got the boat from.

07:03.287 --> 07:07.287
That rotted-out rowboat.

07:08.911 --> 07:12.911
Can we see the documentation on the lawsuit?

07:15.699 --> 07:19.699
Help yourself.

07:22.161 --> 07:26.895
You said that things had gotten
difficult for your wife.

07:26.895 --> 07:29.364
We got an offer to settle.

07:29.364 --> 07:30.841
There was a lot of pressure.

07:30.841 --> 07:34.841
- From the other parents?
- Yes. Brian could have been saved.

07:35.796 --> 07:38.311
They all could have.

07:38.311 --> 07:41.002
Is this your wife's handwriting?

07:41.002 --> 07:44.648
- Yes.
- Most of the notes are hers.

07:45.148 --> 07:48.717
She was the driving force, wasn't she?

07:49.217 --> 07:51.241
She's the one that didn't want to settle.

07:51.241 --> 07:53.714
Laura wanted them punished.

07:53.714 --> 07:57.428
Anyone who had anything
to do with Brian's death,

07:57.428 --> 08:01.092
she wanted them punished.

08:01.592 --> 08:03.830
Like it's anybody's fault.
Those kids were stupid.

08:03.830 --> 08:06.280
I mean, stealing a rowboat from the repair yard.

08:06.280 --> 08:07.942
What did they expect?

08:07.942 --> 08:11.340
- And the boat was behind that fence?
- Uh-huh. It was takin' on water.

08:11.840 --> 08:14.351
Saturday afternoon, you
or any of the other guys

08:14.351 --> 08:16.107
go to St. Brendan's for the meeting?

08:16.107 --> 08:19.676
Saturday afternoon we spent scraping that sloop.

08:19.676 --> 08:27.152
You know, this photo was taken
the day after the drowning.

08:27.152 --> 08:29.828
See these drag marks?

08:29.828 --> 08:36.860
They say the boys pushed
the rowboat into the water from,

08:36.860 --> 08:39.400
well, I'd say right about here.

08:39.400 --> 08:40.807
Yeah, but that boat wasn't here.

08:40.807 --> 08:43.505
It was in the yard behind the fence.

08:43.505 --> 08:45.038
Well, maybe it's a different boat.

08:45.038 --> 08:47.738
No, it's the same boat.
The harbor cops found it.

08:47.738 --> 08:50.906
That's Hart Island, huh?
That's where they were heading.

08:50.906 --> 08:52.095
On account of the cemetery.

08:52.095 --> 08:55.098
Kids think it's fun to drink and
carry on with the dead,

08:55.098 --> 08:58.535
the little heathen bastards.

08:59.035 --> 09:02.096
This, uh, leaky rowboat...

09:02.096 --> 09:04.873
it would've started taking
on water as soon as they set off.

09:04.873 --> 09:06.817
There would've been three inches
of water on the bottom...

09:06.817 --> 09:09.208
before they even reached the end of that dock.

09:09.208 --> 09:13.208
I don't see why they kept on going.

09:21.395 --> 09:23.175
I can't tell you how sorry we are, Mike.

09:23.175 --> 09:24.952
Thank you.

09:24.952 --> 09:27.527
You come over for dinner this weekend.

09:27.527 --> 09:31.527
Well, you see how you feel.

09:33.764 --> 09:35.853
Listen, Mike, about the settlement...

09:35.853 --> 09:38.262
we'd all feel better if it's unanimous.

09:38.262 --> 09:40.308
- We know how Laura felt...
- No, it's all right,

09:40.308 --> 09:41.150
it's all right, it's all right.

09:41.150 --> 09:45.150
Just tell the lawyers I'll sign off. It's fine.

09:50.381 --> 09:53.301
Mrs. Koehler was...

09:53.301 --> 09:55.734
so nice to me, sir.

09:55.734 --> 09:59.734
I know she liked you.

10:06.797 --> 10:10.103
I passed the photos of
the marina employees around.

10:10.103 --> 10:11.607
No one saw them at St. Brendan's.

10:11.607 --> 10:14.216
Well, they'd have been there
if St. Brendan's had happy hour.

10:14.216 --> 10:18.216
I ran their sheets.
Mostly drunk and disorderlies, bar fights.

10:20.577 --> 10:22.011
Want me to stick a dart in him?

10:22.011 --> 10:27.184
No. He's listening to the tape of
the 911 call the kids made from the boat.

10:30.002 --> 10:33.439
L-I need to see the boat.

10:33.439 --> 10:35.887
We were storing it in case there was a trial,

10:35.887 --> 10:38.907
but I got word yesterday
that the parties settled.

10:38.907 --> 10:41.889
Someone worried the boat'll float away?

10:41.889 --> 10:43.587
Can't be too sure.

10:43.587 --> 10:45.975
Last place we had it,
someone tried to break in.

10:45.975 --> 10:47.536
911.
What is your emergency?

10:47.536 --> 10:49.956
Our boat's filling up with water!
You gotta send help.!

10:49.956 --> 10:51.248
- What is your location?
- I don't know.

10:51.248 --> 10:53.253
Off Channel Island, 200 yards.

10:53.253 --> 10:56.767
It just started, and it started leaking
in the front. It's leaking like crazy!

10:56.767 --> 10:58.852
- Sir, I need a location.
- Channel Island!

10:58.852 --> 11:00.568
The front of the boat is filling up!

11:00.568 --> 11:04.567
Help us! We're sinking!
We're gonna drown! Help!

11:04.567 --> 11:09.811
Those kids, two minutes in that
freezing water, they were done for.

11:09.811 --> 11:14.195
The wood along the seams
has been rotted out.

11:14.195 --> 11:17.868
This boat should've sank like
a stone as soon as it hit the water.

11:18.650 --> 11:22.650
And there's a kind of... residue...

11:25.237 --> 11:29.237
stuck in the cracks.

11:36.342 --> 11:39.802
Um, uh, cake frosting...

11:40.302 --> 11:44.302
and something else.

11:46.665 --> 11:49.808
It's white glue.

11:49.808 --> 11:54.095
Someone patched the seams with
a mixture of frosting and glue.

11:54.095 --> 11:57.179
Wouldn't frosting dissolve
on contact with water?

11:57.179 --> 11:59.018
That's why they used the glue.

11:59.018 --> 12:02.324
It... It hardens.

12:02.324 --> 12:04.301
It would protect the patches

12:04.301 --> 12:08.301
just long enough for
the boat to get far from shore.

12:12.109 --> 12:14.378
Too far to swim back.

12:14.378 --> 12:17.134
Someone wanted it to sink.

12:17.134 --> 12:19.723
They moved the boat from the repair yard,

12:19.723 --> 12:21.628
they patched it up,

12:21.628 --> 12:23.999
put it where the kids would find it,

12:23.999 --> 12:27.999
knowing that it would never
be able to cross the sound.

12:30.297 --> 12:34.100
Those kids were murdered.

12:34.600 --> 12:36.625
Sabotage?
Somebody killed our boys?

12:36.625 --> 12:40.653
Yes. This person might have been worried
the sabotage would be discovered...

12:40.653 --> 12:43.392
if your lawsuit went to trial.

12:43.392 --> 12:45.982
We believe that's why Laura was killed.

12:45.982 --> 12:48.414
Oh, God.

12:48.414 --> 12:50.278
She didn't want to settle.
She wanted it to go to trial.

12:50.278 --> 12:51.976
That's what you told us.

12:51.976 --> 12:53.531
They were headed to the cemetery.

12:53.531 --> 12:57.043
Do you know if they had any
interest in Satanism or witchcraft?

12:57.043 --> 12:59.147
No! These were just average kids.

12:59.147 --> 13:00.725
Maybe we could ask their girlfriends.

13:00.725 --> 13:03.225
Brian wasn't seeing anyone in particular.

13:03.225 --> 13:05.258
And John wasn't either.
He said these days

13:05.258 --> 13:09.258
it wasn't cool to go steady with any one person.

13:10.134 --> 13:13.546
All right. Thank you all for coming in.

13:13.546 --> 13:17.546
The officer will show you downstairs.

13:22.652 --> 13:25.144
I'd hate to think we put 'em
through that for nothing.

13:25.144 --> 13:26.579
Any luck tracing the arsenic?

13:26.579 --> 13:30.192
The lab can't match it to any
commercial arsenic currently available.

13:30.192 --> 13:33.742
I'm looking at Brian Koehler's autopsy.

13:33.742 --> 13:37.273
He had gonorrhea.

13:37.273 --> 13:40.764
So did his other two friends.

13:40.764 --> 13:44.437
Now, what are the odds of three 17-year-olds...

13:44.437 --> 13:48.230
having the same sexually transmitted disease?

13:48.230 --> 13:49.998
Office of Medical Examiner
Monday, May 26

13:49.998 --> 13:52.371
The gonorrhea of all three boys had the same D.N.A.

13:52.371 --> 13:53.884
Could they have gotten it from each other?

13:53.884 --> 13:57.884
It's doubtful. Autopsies showed
no rectal or oral infection.

13:59.470 --> 14:01.533
Well, they got it from the same girl.

14:01.533 --> 14:05.533
Unless toilet seats and doorknobs
are making a comeback.

14:07.363 --> 14:09.164
Three boys with the same girl.

14:09.164 --> 14:10.192
What if it was rape?

14:10.192 --> 14:11.831
They might have been murdered in revenge.

14:11.831 --> 14:13.222
We need to find this girl.

14:13.222 --> 14:15.810
She probably didn't file a rape
complaint against any of the boys.

14:15.810 --> 14:18.914
We would've heard about it.

14:18.914 --> 14:20.266
The church meeting.

14:20.266 --> 14:24.266
There were a couple of girls
helping with the coffee and cookies.

14:24.767 --> 14:28.110
I've known Tina and Carolyn since
they were in the children's choir.

14:28.110 --> 14:28.876
I'm sure they're not...

14:28.876 --> 14:33.221
I'm wondering what kind of kid would
give up their Saturday afternoon

14:33.221 --> 14:35.269
for a church function.
You don't pay them, do you?

14:35.269 --> 14:36.642
No. They volunteered.

14:36.642 --> 14:38.255
Do they belong to a church group?

14:38.255 --> 14:40.448
Tina did until a few months ago.

14:40.448 --> 14:43.663
She was an altar girl.
She helped with our youth outreach.

14:43.663 --> 14:49.078
- She had a child's devotion to God.
- And that... that changed?

14:49.078 --> 14:50.799
She got the teenage blues, I guess.

14:50.799 --> 14:53.704
She just stopped coming to church.

14:53.704 --> 14:56.606
And that was around the time
that the boys drowned?

14:56.606 --> 14:59.118
No, a few weeks before.

14:59.118 --> 15:02.224
But now she seems her old self again.
Very happy.

15:02.224 --> 15:05.622
Whatever was bothering
her worked itself out.

15:06.122 --> 15:09.049
I didn't see anybody mess with the food.

15:09.049 --> 15:12.747
But I wasn't watching the whole time.

15:13.247 --> 15:17.235
Okay, Tina. That about covers it.

15:17.735 --> 15:24.210
Mrs. Hale said that you had
drifted away from the church for a while.

15:26.490 --> 15:30.490
I did the same thing when I was her age.

15:31.342 --> 15:33.746
You know, I just couldn't see
what all that stuffhad

15:33.746 --> 15:37.746
to do with my life anymore, you know.

15:38.848 --> 15:41.382
Is that what happened to you, Tina?

15:41.382 --> 15:44.586
I just needed some space.

15:44.586 --> 15:48.586
Did something make you realize that?

15:49.463 --> 15:52.464
Nothing in particular.

15:52.464 --> 15:56.464
Was it those boys drowning?

16:02.836 --> 16:06.836
Did you think that God didn't care?

16:07.509 --> 16:09.757
He let your friends die.

16:09.757 --> 16:12.962
I didn't hang with those guys.

16:12.962 --> 16:15.270
Why not?

16:15.270 --> 16:18.278
They're delta heads.

16:18.278 --> 16:22.278
You know, like totally asleep up there.

16:23.032 --> 16:25.252
There are three levels of sleep:

16:25.252 --> 16:33.080
Alpha, theta and delta.
That's like... deep sleep.

16:37.060 --> 16:40.183
Where'd you learn that?

16:40.183 --> 16:44.183
I don't know.

16:46.543 --> 16:53.055
Um...So what made you
stop going to church?

16:53.055 --> 16:55.464
Did something happen to you, Tina?

16:55.464 --> 16:59.464
Something Brian and the other boys did?

17:00.461 --> 17:04.461
- No. I needed some space.
- All right, that's enough.

17:05.371 --> 17:09.371
Tina, you're excused.

17:12.422 --> 17:16.035
Where did you get this idea that
my daughter was raped?

17:16.035 --> 17:17.632
She would've come to us.

17:17.632 --> 17:19.698
Has she seen a doctor
in the last five months?

17:19.698 --> 17:23.178
She's been to the gynecologist.

17:23.178 --> 17:27.178
What is it you want with my daughter?

17:28.309 --> 17:30.682
I see.

17:30.682 --> 17:32.272
You're getting out of our house.

17:32.272 --> 17:36.272
