He was jealous of those boys.

35:12.385 --> 35:14.673
But we'd like to know
what he said to your daughters.

35:14.673 --> 35:16.658
He didn't say anything.

35:16.658 --> 35:17.932
He didn't do it.

35:17.932 --> 35:20.375
You know what? He's lucky,
because if it weren't for Claudia,

35:20.375 --> 35:23.032
he'd be facing the death penalty.

35:23.032 --> 35:26.888
She saved his life.

35:27.388 --> 35:29.121
You just take a good look at this girl,

35:29.121 --> 35:33.121
and you can see the depths
of her devotion to him.

35:34.957 --> 35:38.957
He has to know that
she's his one true friend.

35:40.182 --> 35:43.986
Probably the only friend he has left.

35:44.486 --> 35:46.730
Connie didn't make those guys drown.

35:46.730 --> 35:48.576
- I did.
- Tina, shut up.

35:48.576 --> 35:49.997
Hey, that's okay. We don't believe her.

35:49.997 --> 35:52.939
It's true. I told them to meet me
on Hart Island for a party.

35:52.939 --> 35:54.117
I messed with that boat.

35:54.117 --> 35:56.421
I put stuff in the cracks,
so it wouldn't sink right away.

35:56.421 --> 35:58.088
That's not gonna fly.

35:58.088 --> 36:00.026
- I can prove it.
- Not another word!

36:00.026 --> 36:02.297
I will not let you throw your life away
for some little freak!

36:02.297 --> 36:03.884
He's not a freak!

36:03.884 --> 36:06.606
He knows things!
More things than you do!

36:06.606 --> 36:09.830
He's special. He showed us
how we can be happy

36:09.830 --> 36:13.830
and control our life, and he never
asked us for anything.

36:15.493 --> 36:17.639
I can prove I did it.

36:17.639 --> 36:20.058
You go to my dad's tool shed.

36:20.058 --> 36:22.651
You'll see.

36:22.651 --> 36:25.349
I want to see this alleged
statement against my client.

36:25.349 --> 36:26.446
All in good time.

36:26.446 --> 36:28.960
I'm warning you, Mr. Carver.

36:28.960 --> 36:31.950
I won't put up with any tricks.

36:31.950 --> 36:33.419
How'd the booking go?

36:33.419 --> 36:36.464
He was a perfect young gentleman.

36:36.464 --> 36:38.368
That's what everyone says.

36:38.368 --> 36:40.843
Mr. Smith, we're here
to discuss a plea agreement...

36:40.843 --> 36:44.441
on three counts of murder by drowning.

36:44.441 --> 36:46.530
- I didn't kill anyone.
- Hold on.

36:46.530 --> 36:48.413
I want to see that statement.

36:48.413 --> 36:51.763
- What statement?
- One of the girls gave you up.

36:51.763 --> 36:53.769
There's nothing to give up.

36:53.769 --> 36:55.060
I didn't do anything.

36:55.060 --> 36:59.060
What you didn't do yourself,
you told them to do.

36:59.663 --> 37:03.663
I never told anyone to do anything.

37:04.639 --> 37:08.113
Which one do you think
gave you up...Tina or Carolyn?

37:08.113 --> 37:10.646
Neither of them would say
anything against me.

37:10.646 --> 37:14.272
Why? You're not allowed
to speak against the prophet?

37:14.772 --> 37:17.306
- I'm nobody's prophet.
- No, see, they think you are.

37:17.306 --> 37:19.329
They think you're teaching them to,

37:19.329 --> 37:21.440
well, control their world, you know.

37:21.440 --> 37:25.032
But the joke is on them, right?

37:25.032 --> 37:28.420
I can't teach anyone anything.

37:28.920 --> 37:30.805
No, you just listen.

37:30.805 --> 37:33.754
Is that right?

37:33.754 --> 37:38.059
All these kids, you know,
taking drugs, uh, drinking,

37:38.059 --> 37:40.107
having the sex parties,

37:40.107 --> 37:43.874
while you just wait with
your little fishing rod,

37:44.374 --> 37:48.203
and you hook whatever damaged
goods comes out of the pit.

37:48.703 --> 37:51.527
Their parents made them what they are.
I didn't do anything.

37:51.527 --> 37:53.480
And when those girls wanted to hurt

37:53.480 --> 37:56.914
those mean boys who debased them,

38:00.020 --> 38:01.801
- then you did something.
- No.

38:01.801 --> 38:03.733
You exploited their anger.

38:03.733 --> 38:07.374
And after you helped them kill,
you exploited their fear.

38:07.874 --> 38:10.223
Mr. Carver, if I don't see that statement,

38:10.223 --> 38:12.129
- we're not continuing.
- You walk out that door,

38:12.129 --> 38:14.796
- any chance of a plea bargain goes with you.
- Come on.

38:14.796 --> 38:19.281
Just tell me which one, Connie.
Tina or Carolyn?

38:19.281 --> 38:22.607
Look, I don't kill for myself.

38:22.607 --> 38:25.387
And for sure I wouldn't kill for them.

38:25.387 --> 38:28.088
There's nothing in it for me.

38:28.088 --> 38:32.273
There's admiration,
because special people like admirers,

38:32.273 --> 38:35.897
and... and you're special.

38:36.397 --> 38:40.397
- Well, aren't you, Connie?
- I'm not...

38:41.101 --> 38:44.022
I'm not that special.

38:44.022 --> 38:46.906
Well, I think you made yourself special.

38:46.906 --> 38:50.864
I think that's the lie you told yourself
to explain why your mother ditched you.

38:51.364 --> 38:54.592
No. That's not reality.

38:54.592 --> 38:56.820
My mother has important work.

38:56.820 --> 39:00.820
Like cleaning motel rooms in Laughlin?

39:01.476 --> 39:04.999
Well, here's her number,
if you want to call her.

39:04.999 --> 39:09.831
Oh, look, look!
Bing! Reality!

39:14.066 --> 39:18.066
People leave you.
Your mother, soon your uncle.

39:19.028 --> 39:23.028
I don't let that stuff bother me.

39:23.541 --> 39:25.113
Oh.

39:25.113 --> 39:26.791
I've got myself.

39:26.791 --> 39:30.567
The rest of the world can just fade away.

39:30.567 --> 39:32.107
I don't care.

39:32.107 --> 39:34.438
'Cause you're all alone,
like a star in the heavens,

39:34.438 --> 39:38.438
overcome by an icy despair,
but more firmly yourself than ever.

39:39.848 --> 39:42.038
Isn't that what you're tryin' to tell me?

39:42.038 --> 39:44.268
You see, unlike the girls,

39:44.268 --> 39:47.924
you know, I've read the book,
so don't try and con me.

39:48.424 --> 39:52.424
The reason you only have yourself is
'cause you have no choice.

39:54.158 --> 39:58.158
And you don't trust anyone.

39:59.628 --> 40:02.488
And this is why.

40:02.488 --> 40:05.046
There's nothing on that piece of paper.

40:05.046 --> 40:06.218
I know who I can trust.

40:06.218 --> 40:08.877
Come on! You were bringing
the two girls to Utah, right?

40:08.877 --> 40:11.688
'Cause if one of'em betrays you,
then you still have the other one.

40:11.688 --> 40:13.328
Those things don't happen to me.

40:13.328 --> 40:16.355
No? Well, they happen to every prophet.

40:16.355 --> 40:19.133
And if you learned anything
from reading these books,

40:19.133 --> 40:22.721
you should've learned that.

40:23.221 --> 40:25.572
No one betrays me.

40:25.572 --> 40:28.901
Come on. Tina or Carolyn?

40:28.901 --> 40:29.971
No one betrays me.

40:29.971 --> 40:31.914
Think again!

40:31.914 --> 40:33.305
We got the smoking gun.

40:33.305 --> 40:37.305
The smoking... caulking gun.

40:39.106 --> 40:40.927
The one used to patch up the boat.

40:40.927 --> 40:44.544
The one that still has traces of
cake frosting and glue on it.

40:45.044 --> 40:46.805
You ready to answer that question now?

40:46.805 --> 40:49.259
It can't be.
I told her to clean it off.

40:49.259 --> 40:53.259
Come on.! Answer.!
Tina or Carolyn?

40:56.411 --> 41:00.411
- What'd you do to her?
- Answer!

41:01.539 --> 41:04.724
It's... It's...

41:04.724 --> 41:08.430
Tina.

41:08.930 --> 41:10.907
Tina! All right?

41:10.907 --> 41:12.872
It's Tina!

41:12.872 --> 41:14.530
She was mine!

41:14.530 --> 41:15.823
What did you do to her?

41:15.823 --> 41:18.663
Well, it's like the book says:

41:18.663 --> 41:22.663
That every sin carries grace within it.

41:27.768 --> 41:28.940
Ouch.

41:28.940 --> 41:32.292
You took her from me.
You took her from me.

41:32.292 --> 41:35.723
I should take this thing and beat
your brains in with it...

41:35.723 --> 41:37.729
'cause that's what you deserve,

41:37.729 --> 41:39.938
what you all deserve!

41:39.938 --> 41:42.637
There's more just like her,

41:42.637 --> 41:45.620
ready to crawl out of that pit...

41:45.620 --> 41:47.686
and come at you with knives...

41:47.686 --> 41:49.817
'cause that's what you deserve.

41:49.817 --> 41:53.238
That's what you deserve.
That's what you deserve!

41:53.238 --> 41:56.644
Get off me.! Get off!

41:57.144 --> 41:59.136
Arraignment Court
Part 22
Friday, June 6

41:59.136 --> 42:00.705
The defendant is remanded

42:00.705 --> 42:03.321
to the custody of
the Department of Correction,

42:03.321 --> 42:06.222
pending completion of a sentencing report.

42:06.222 --> 42:07.430
Next case.

42:07.430 --> 42:09.867
People v. Christina Walker and Carolyn James.

42:09.867 --> 42:13.316
Murder in the second degree, six counts.

42:13.316 --> 42:15.221
Connie! Connie! You'll be okay!

42:15.221 --> 42:16.595
You be quiet, young ladies.!

42:16.595 --> 42:17.888
We told them what happened.

42:17.888 --> 42:19.198
We told them we did it.

42:19.198 --> 42:23.198
Me and Carolyn,
we killed those pigs.

42:24.264 --> 42:26.697
We love you, Connie.

42:26.697 --> 42:30.697
Bailiff, will you take these people out
and bring in the next case?

42:34.961 --> 42:36.478
We're the only reality.

42:36.478 --> 42:40.478
The reality's inside us, right, Connie?

42:57.274 --> 42:59.016
He didn't look too happy.

42:59.016 --> 43:03.016
Reality caught up with him.

43:06.882 --> 43:10.599
Reality catches up with everybody.

